olive oil
3 clove garlic
20 g butter
1 packet basmati rice
1.5 cup water
¼ tsp salt
1 onion
1 capsicum
1 carrot
1 sachet Mumbai Spice Blend
1 tin coconut milk
1 sachet vegetable stock powder
1 tsp brown sugar
1 bag baby spinach leaves
1 bag coriander
1 packet roasted cashews
½ packet Veggie Mince

Finely chop the garlic. In a medium saucepan,
melt the butter with a dash of olive oil over a
medium heat. Cook 1/2 the garlic until fragrant,
1-2 minutes. Add the basmati rice, water and the
salt, stir, then bring to the boil. Reduce the heat to
low and cover with a lid. Cook for 10 minutes, then
remove from the heat and keep covered until the
rice is tender and the water is absorbed,
10 minutes.
TIP: The rice will finish cooking in its own steam so
don't peek!

While the garlic rice is cooking, finely chop the red
onion. Roughly chop the capsicum. Thinly slice the
carrot into half-moons.

In a large frying pan heat a drizzle of olive oil over
a medium-high heat. Add the onion, season with
salt and cook until softened slightly, 2-3 minutes.

Add the veggie mince (see ingredients), capsicum
and carrot and cook, stirring occasionally,
until softened, 2-3 minutes. Add the Mumbai
spice blend and remaining garlic and cook
until fragrant, 1 minute. Add the coconut milk,
vegetable stock powder and brown sugar, then
bring to a simmer. Reduce heat to medium-low and
simmer until the veggies are tender,
3-4 minutes.

Remove the frying pan from the heat, then stir
through the baby spinach leaves until wilted,
1 minute. Season to taste.

Roughly chop the coriander. Divide the garlic
rice between bowls. Top with the Bombay veggie
mince and coconut curry. Garnish with the roasted
cashews and coriander.